Package org.sbml.jsbml

Class CVTerm

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.sbml.jsbml.AbstractTreeNode
      • org.sbml.jsbml.AnnotationElement
        • org.sbml.jsbml.CVTerm
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, javax.swing.tree.TreeNode, TreeNodeWithChangeSupport

    public class CVTerm
extends AnnotationElement
    Contains all the MIRIAM URIs for a MIRIAM qualifier in the annotation element of a SBML component.
    Since:
    0.8
    Author:
    Andreas Dräger, Marine Dumousseau, Nicolas Rodriguez
    See Also:
    Serialized Form

      • filterResources

        public java.util.List<java.lang.String> filterResources​(java.util.regex.Pattern... patterns)
        Returns a list of resource URIs that contain the given Pattern(s). This is useful to obtain, e.g., all KEGG resources this term points to.
        Parameters:
        patterns - an arbitrary number of Pattern(s), e.g., http://identifiers.org/kegg.reaction/R.*, .*kegg.* or just kegg that are matched to all resources using an OR-operation, i.e., if just one of the patterns matches a resource, this resource will appear in the returned list.
        Returns:
        A list of all resources that contain the given pattern. This list can be empty, but never null. The order of the resources in that list will be identical to the order in this term.
        See Also:
        Pattern, Matcher.find()

      • filterResources

        public java.util.List<java.lang.String> filterResources​(java.lang.String... patterns)
        Returns a list of resource URIs that contain the given pattern(s). This is useful to obtain, e.g., all KEGG resources this term points to.
        Parameters:
        patterns - an arbitrary number of patterns, e.g., http://idenifiers.org/kegg.reaction/R.*, .*kegg.* or just kegg that are matched to all resources using an OR-operation, i.e., if just one of the patterns matches a resource, this resource will appear in the returned list.
        Returns:
        A list of all resources that contain the given pattern. This list can be empty, but never null. The order of the resources in that list will be identical to the order in this CVTerm.

        Pattern, Matcher.find()

      • getQualifier

        public CVTerm.Qualifier getQualifier​()
        Returns the CVTerm.Qualifier for this CVTerm.

        If you want to know if the Qualifier is a model qualifier or a biological modifier, you can use CVTerm.Qualifier.isModelQualifier() and CVTerm.Qualifier.isBiologicalQualifier().

        If you want to display the name of the Qualifier, you can use CVTerm.Qualifier.getElementNameEquivalent().

        Returns:
        the CVTerm.Qualifier for this CVTerm.

        public void setUnknownQualifierName​(java.lang.String unknownQualifierName)
